      "writtenOn": "2026-05-05T06:28:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As per DMTF DSP0248 v1.3.0, Table 52, the compositeEffecterCount field specifies the number of state effecter sets accessed by the command, with a valid range of 0x01 to 0x08.\n\nSince the command always includes at least one composite effecter, PLDM_SET_STATE_EFFECTER_STATES_MIN_REQ_BYTES already accounts for the first composite effecter.\n\nTherefore, when calculating the total request size, we use (effecterCount − 1) to account only for the additional composite effecters beyond the first one that is already included.\n\nReferences : https://www.dmtf.org/sites/default/files/standards/documents/DSP0248_1.3.0.pdf",
